25/04/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The government and the European Network and Information Security Agency (ENISA) sealed an agreement Friday (22 April) that base the ENISA headquarters on the Crete island town of Iraklio.
After the signing ceremony, Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis said Greek authorities are committed to the prevention of network and information security breaches.
In other news, officials announced that a new daily railway link connecting Istanbul and Thessaloniki, Greece, is expected to become operational shortly.
An agreement will be signed next month in Ankara.
(Kathimerini, ANA - 23/04/05)
